@node Top, Introduction, (dir), (dir)

@center The SB-Prolog System, Version 2.5
@center A User Manual
@sp 5
@center @b{ABSTRACT}
@sp 2
SB-Prolog is a Prolog system for Unix based systems.  The core of the  system
is  an  emulator,  written  in C for portability, of a Prolog virtual machine that is an
extension of the Warren Abstract Machine.  The remainder of the  system,  including  the
translator from Prolog to the virtual machine instructions, is written in Prolog.  Parts
of this manual, specifically the sections on Prolog syntax and descriptions of  some  of
the builtins, are based on the C-Prolog User Manual by Fernando Pereira.@REFILL

